name: Palingenesia CD Album (Field Records)
description: "Khuda are a heavy instrumental post-rock influenced two-piece band from Leeds U.K. with comparisons made to the post-rock influenced sound of bands like Russian Circles or Pelican, the heaviness of a duo like 5ive and the math-rock of Don Caballero. Releasing two EP's to date, recently they have recorded their first full-length album "Palingenesia" at Ghosttown Studios in Leeds, and mastered by Carl Saff (Young widows, OM, Grails etc) in the U.S. and will be released on Nov 1st  in time for the tour on CD and Digitally by Field Records and vinyl by Mannheim's Pruegelprinz Records."

name: Stratospherics - CDEP [2009]
description:
STRATOSPHERICS BY KHUDA, Norrland Recordings [2009]

TRACKLISTING

01. Ezra
02. Hester Panim
03. Spirit
04. Arrival

Khuda are an instrumental two-piece from Leeds, UK. They have been making noise together since March 2007 and have progressed their sound greatly since then into a multi-amped mix of dark progressions and peaks, releasing two EP’s to date. Now, after a period of change... Khuda are planning to tour as much as possible in 2009/10. Stratospherics features the last material written with original drummer Robin Timmis.

All Music Written And Performed By Tom Brooke + Robin Timmis

Recorded in April 2009 by Ross Halden (Ghost Town Recordings)

Mastered by Carl Saff (Saff Mastering)

The CD version features artwork from Helder Pedro 
(www.helderpedro.com)
